00:43:01.361 --> 00:43:02.480 align:middle line:90%
Plato had it right.

00:43:02.480 --> 00:43:06.360 align:middle line:84%
We light-skinned humans
are from the deepest

00:43:06.360 --> 00:43:09.360 align:middle line:84%
parts of the previously
exposed landscape.

00:43:09.360 --> 00:43:10.320 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:43:10.320 --> 00:43:11.730 align:middle line:90%
Why are we light skinned?

00:43:11.730 --> 00:43:14.310 align:middle line:84%
Because the atmosphere,
which would have fallen down

00:43:14.310 --> 00:43:18.900 align:middle line:84%
in there, would have
attenuated away the ultraviolet

00:43:18.900 --> 00:43:20.320 align:middle line:90%
and blue light waves.

00:43:20.320 --> 00:43:21.420 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Good point.

00:43:21.420 --> 00:43:23.190 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: In fact,
a recent finding

00:43:23.190 --> 00:43:26.672 align:middle line:84%
is that some humans didn't
see blue until only recently.

00:43:26.672 --> 00:43:27.630 align:middle line:90%
Well, that explains it.

00:43:27.630 --> 00:43:30.490 align:middle line:84%
The blue wavelengths would
have been attenuated away

00:43:30.490 --> 00:43:31.290 align:middle line:90%
by the atmosphere.

00:43:31.290 --> 00:43:32.310 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:43:32.310 --> 00:43:34.020 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: So lighter
skinned humans

00:43:34.020 --> 00:43:37.260 align:middle line:84%
are from the deepest
part of the Atlantic.

00:43:37.260 --> 00:43:39.630 align:middle line:84%
Darker skinned humans, they
had more need for melanin.

00:43:39.630 --> 00:43:43.290 align:middle line:84%
They would have come from
probably more tropical regions

00:43:43.290 --> 00:43:45.720 align:middle line:90%
and higher regions.

00:43:45.720 --> 00:43:48.380 align:middle line:84%
So we can explain human
skin pigmentation.

00:43:48.380 --> 00:43:49.580 align:middle line:90%
We can explain Lemuria.

00:43:49.580 --> 00:43:51.380 align:middle line:90%
We can explain Atlantis.

00:43:51.380 --> 00:43:55.160 align:middle line:84%
We can explain what we're
properly adapted for.

00:43:55.160 --> 00:43:57.950 align:middle line:84%
So the story of Adam and
Eve with the naked humans,

00:43:57.950 --> 00:43:59.270 align:middle line:90%
we're living in Eden.

00:43:59.270 --> 00:44:01.535 align:middle line:84%
They're the landscapes for
which we were properly--

00:44:01.535 --> 00:44:02.766 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: A real story.

00:44:02.766 --> 00:44:04.640 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: --for which we
were properly adapted.

00:44:04.640 --> 00:44:07.190 align:middle line:84%
The snake, Satan--
so this object

00:44:07.190 --> 00:44:10.190 align:middle line:84%
that hit the Earth has several
names in the various cultures.

00:44:10.190 --> 00:44:14.500 align:middle line:84%
It is known as Phaethon,
Set, and Satan--

00:44:14.500 --> 00:44:15.770 align:middle line:90%
Satan.

00:44:15.770 --> 00:44:17.567 align:middle line:84%
When I saw that it
was called Satan,

00:44:17.567 --> 00:44:18.900 align:middle line:90%
I just had one of these moments.

00:44:18.900 --> 00:44:20.290 align:middle line:90%
I'll be darned.

00:44:20.290 --> 00:44:21.410 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: An aha moment.

00:44:21.410 --> 00:44:23.720 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: So the serpent
is just an allegory

00:44:23.720 --> 00:44:27.410 align:middle line:84%
for the object, the snake-like
object as it appeared,

00:44:27.410 --> 00:44:28.374 align:middle line:90%
as it came into Earth.

00:44:28.374 --> 00:44:29.960 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: As it was coming in.

00:44:29.960 --> 00:44:31.043 align:middle line:90%
>>JAYE: There you have it.

00:44:31.043 --> 00:44:32.450 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Atlantis, Lemuria.

00:44:32.450 --> 00:44:37.550 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: So that star, those
are the canals of Atlantis.

00:44:37.550 --> 00:44:41.060 align:middle line:84%
Roughly on each
edge, it's 80 miles.

00:44:41.060 --> 00:44:43.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is
that perfect square?

00:44:43.190 --> 00:44:45.800 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: So those are
the canals of Atlantis.

00:44:45.800 --> 00:44:47.540 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Those were man made.

00:44:47.540 --> 00:44:49.610 align:middle line:84%
Nothing could happen
naturally like that.

00:44:49.610 --> 00:44:50.568 align:middle line:90%
>>JAYE: So there we go.

00:44:50.568 --> 00:44:53.884 align:middle line:10%
So if Mr. Ballard wants
to use his equipment

00:44:53.884 --> 00:44:55.550 align:middle line:10%
to go and investigate
a particular area,

00:44:55.550 --> 00:44:58.070 align:middle line:10%
I'd be happy to talk to
him about very special--

00:44:58.070 --> 00:45:00.546 align:middle line:10%
I mean, I believe there's going
to be pyramids down there.

00:45:00.546 --> 00:45:01.420 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It could be.

00:45:01.420 --> 00:45:04.010 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: So the people
of Atlantis were carving

00:45:04.010 --> 00:45:05.330 align:middle line:90%
for thousands--

00:45:05.330 --> 00:45:08.544 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's over essentially
1,000 miles of canals

00:45:08.544 --> 00:45:09.460 align:middle line:90%
that we're looking at.

00:45:09.460 --> 00:45:11.335 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that's all
submerged now, right?

00:45:11.335 --> 00:45:13.730 align:middle line:90%
>>JAYE: It is under three miles.

00:45:13.730 --> 00:45:17.930 align:middle line:84%
The star, it shows one
of the seamounts there.

00:45:17.930 --> 00:45:21.110 align:middle line:84%
It's over 4,000 meters
below present sea level.

00:45:21.110 --> 00:45:23.540 align:middle line:10%
It takes special equipment
to get down there.

00:45:23.540 --> 00:45:25.040 align:middle line:84%
So those are the
canals of Atlantis.

00:45:25.040 --> 00:45:29.000 align:middle line:84%
And they match very closely
with Plato's description.

00:45:29.000 --> 00:45:31.500 align:middle line:84%
He tells us they wound
around the plain.

00:45:31.500 --> 00:45:32.360 align:middle line:90%
They were straight.

00:45:32.360 --> 00:45:34.490 align:middle line:84%
They were 10,000
stadia in length.

00:45:34.490 --> 00:45:37.080 align:middle line:84%
So a stadia is
roughly 200 yards.

00:45:37.080 --> 00:45:37.880 align:middle line:90%
You do the math.

00:45:37.880 --> 00:45:42.270 align:middle line:90%


00:45:42.270 --> 00:45:44.210 align:middle line:90%
It's 1,000 miles.

00:45:44.210 --> 00:45:45.280 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Square miles?

00:45:45.280 --> 00:45:46.920 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: No, 1,000
miles of canals.

00:45:46.920 --> 00:45:47.720 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Jeez.

00:45:47.720 --> 00:45:49.850 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: And so what
I did is I took--

00:45:49.850 --> 00:45:54.050 align:middle line:84%
with ArcGIS, you can
actually measure lengths.

00:45:54.050 --> 00:45:57.260 align:middle line:84%
So I laid, end to end,
straight lines over those.

00:45:57.260 --> 00:45:58.100 align:middle line:90%
And I measured.

00:45:58.100 --> 00:45:58.910 align:middle line:90%
And I'll be darned.

00:45:58.910 --> 00:46:02.771 align:middle line:84%
It's within 4% of
Plato's description.

00:46:02.771 --> 00:46:03.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's amazing.

00:46:03.770 --> 00:46:05.750 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: It is,
Plato's description

00:46:05.750 --> 00:46:07.040 align:middle line:90%
of the canals of Atlantis.

00:46:07.040 --> 00:46:09.930 align:middle line:84%
Now Google, unfortunately we
can't see these on Google.

00:46:09.930 --> 00:46:14.180 align:middle line:84%
So when the maps first
came out, so many people

00:46:14.180 --> 00:46:18.590 align:middle line:84%
were hitting on
this that Google,

00:46:18.590 --> 00:46:22.850 align:middle line:84%
and with others,
they've averaged away

00:46:22.850 --> 00:46:25.640 align:middle line:84%
some of the canals
on the western side.

00:46:25.640 --> 00:46:29.690 align:middle line:84%
But this is available in
NOAA maps, National Oceanic

00:46:29.690 --> 00:46:31.070 align:middle line:90%
Atmospheric Agency.

00:46:31.070 --> 00:46:32.960 align:middle line:84%
This map, if you go
to the Madeira bit,

00:46:32.960 --> 00:46:35.410 align:middle line:84%
