00:46:40.910 --> 00:46:42.440 align:middle line:90%
So you can see Spain.

00:46:42.440 --> 00:46:44.500 align:middle line:90%
You can see Africa.

00:46:44.500 --> 00:46:45.300 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: OK.

00:46:45.300 --> 00:46:46.459 align:middle line:90%
What about Lemuria?

00:46:46.459 --> 00:46:48.500 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: So we know about
Lemuria from a gentleman

00:46:48.500 --> 00:46:50.480 align:middle line:90%
named Churchward.

00:46:50.480 --> 00:46:53.150 align:middle line:84%
Mr. Churchward-- he
was Colonel Churchward.

00:46:53.150 --> 00:46:56.000 align:middle line:90%
He was a British officer.

00:46:56.000 --> 00:46:59.330 align:middle line:84%
And he was admitted
to very special places

00:46:59.330 --> 00:47:03.500 align:middle line:84%
in India and other
temples, if you will,

00:47:03.500 --> 00:47:07.046 align:middle line:90%
where there were writings.

00:47:07.046 --> 00:47:08.420 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to
call them sacred,

00:47:08.420 --> 00:47:10.820 align:middle line:84%
but they were writings,
historical writings

00:47:10.820 --> 00:47:13.490 align:middle line:90%
from the different cultures.

00:47:13.490 --> 00:47:16.100 align:middle line:84%
And from these
cultures, he learned

00:47:16.100 --> 00:47:18.864 align:middle line:90%
about this civilization--

00:47:18.864 --> 00:47:19.780 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What is this?

00:47:19.780 --> 00:47:21.196 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: --that was
called Lemuria.

00:47:21.196 --> 00:47:23.680 align:middle line:84%
What we see here, this
is a DNA heat map.

00:47:23.680 --> 00:47:25.047 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: A DNA heat map?

00:47:25.047 --> 00:47:26.190 align:middle line:90%
>>JAYE: DNA heat map.

00:47:26.190 --> 00:47:28.500 align:middle line:84%
This was published
a couple years ago.

00:47:28.500 --> 00:47:33.620 align:middle line:84%
And what it shows is-- so
in the red and darker colors

00:47:33.620 --> 00:47:37.220 align:middle line:84%
show the largest, the closest
DNA similarities between people

00:47:37.220 --> 00:47:39.770 align:middle line:90%
in Australia and South America.

00:47:39.770 --> 00:47:42.170 align:middle line:84%
Yet, there is no
DNA similarities

00:47:42.170 --> 00:47:44.970 align:middle line:84%
through the Americas
or through Asia.

00:47:44.970 --> 00:47:46.970 align:middle line:10%
Well, we're supposed
to believe that somehow

00:47:46.970 --> 00:47:51.140 align:middle line:10%
during a hypothesized ice age
when the oceans supposedly

00:47:51.140 --> 00:47:53.930 align:middle line:10%
sank, that these people
down in warm cultures

00:47:53.930 --> 00:47:56.390 align:middle line:10%
are going to somehow
cross the Bering Sea

00:47:56.390 --> 00:48:02.000 align:middle line:10%
and travel 20,000 miles by
land from Australia to South

00:48:02.000 --> 00:48:06.500 align:middle line:10%
America, and yet leave no DNA
similarities where they passed?

00:48:06.500 --> 00:48:08.745 align:middle line:84%
That's fantasy
masquerading as science.

00:48:08.745 --> 00:48:09.620 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:48:09.620 --> 00:48:11.340 align:middle line:84%
>>JAYE: So what
happened was Lemuria

