We don't see canals.

00:48:21.409 --> 00:48:22.700 align:middle line:10%
I don't know if we're going to.

00:48:22.700 --> 00:48:25.910 align:middle line:10%
I mean, it's so hard
to see detail that far

00:48:25.910 --> 00:48:27.650 align:middle line:10%
below the surface.

00:48:27.650 --> 00:48:29.690 align:middle line:84%
Are we going to find
civilizations or remnants

00:48:29.690 --> 00:48:31.670 align:middle line:90%
of cities or whatnot in Lemuria?

00:48:31.670 --> 00:48:33.020 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:48:33.020 --> 00:48:38.070 align:middle line:84%
But one of the things we
do see, the survivors.

00:48:38.070 --> 00:48:41.810 align:middle line:84%
Churchward tells us 64
million inhabitants were lost.

00:48:41.810 --> 00:48:43.230 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: 64 million?

00:48:43.230 --> 00:48:44.060 align:middle line:90%
>>JAYE: 64 million.

00:48:44.060 --> 00:48:45.275 align:middle line:90%
He recounts this in his book.

00:48:45.275 --> 00:48:46.320 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wiped out.

00:48:46.320 --> 00:48:47.730 align:middle line:90%
>>JAYE: Were lost in the flood.

